{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":19545,"record_hash":"sha256:e079ba5d251cbe24ef715f2d9fb39f26ceae4b8395531f8a3e6399dc60485927","timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:48:05.564Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes, exactly. I think that is the nice API.\n\nSomething like:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Serialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"kebab-case\")]\nstruct SourceMetadata<'a> {\n    agent: &'a str,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    provider: Option<&'a str>,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    model: Option<&'a str>,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    tool_version: Option<&'a str>,\n}\n\nhandle.put_record(source_prefix, &source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nAnd GitMeta would persist:\n\n```text\n<source-prefix>:agent = ...\n<source-prefix>:provider = ...\n<source-prefix>:model = ...\n<source-prefix>:tool-version = ...\n```\n\nSo yes: the caller passes a whole typed struct, and `git-meta-lib` uses serde field names and serde attributes to decide the persisted keys.\n\nThe important API detail is semantics:\n\n- `put_record(prefix, value)` sounds like it replaces the whole record.\n- `patch_record(prefix, value)` sounds like it only writes fields emitted by serde and leaves omitted fields alone.\n\nOur current behavior is closer to `patch_record`, because `None` fields are skipped rather than deleting previously stored values. So maybe the GitMeta API should eventually have:\n\n```rust\nhandle.patch_record(prefix, &source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nand later, if needed:\n\n```rust\nhandle.replace_record(prefix, &source_metadata)?;\n```\n\nFor this POC, `patch_record` is probably the natural fit. It would remove most of the awkward string-key plumbing from `gitmeta.rs` without hiding set/list operations like `set_add` and `list_push`.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T10:48:05.564Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}